340 g Pork Tenderloin
227 g Broccoli
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Zucchini
1 unit(s) Egg
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
2 tbsp All-Purpose Flour
28 g Almonds, sliced
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 unit(s) Lemon
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
2.5 tbsp Oil*

Roughly chop almonds.
Zest lemon, then cut into wedges.
﻿Pat pork dry with paper towels, then, if applicable, cut into 2 equal pieces  (4 pieces for 4 ppl) on a separate cutting board. Season with salt and pepper.

Add egg and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) warm water to a shallow dish. Whisk to combine.
Add almonds, lemon zest and panko to another shallow dish. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Sprinkle flour over top of pork, turning to coat all sides.
Working with one piece at a time, add pork to the shallow dish with egg mixture, turning to coat all sides. Transfer egg-coated pork to dish with panko mixture.
Turn and press all sides into panko mixture to coat completely.

Transfer crusted pork to a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast pork in the middle of the oven until cooked through, 24-26 min.**

Meanwhile, cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Core, then cut pepper into 2-inch pieces.
Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch rounds.

Add broccoli, peppers , zucchini, Zesty Garlic Blend and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to an unlined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast veggies in the top of the oven until golden brown and tender-crisp, 8-12 min.

Cut pork into thick slices.
Divide pork and veggies between plates.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top, if desired.